--- create all these as test1.py, test2.py, ...

1. Create a program that produces the following output using loops

1000000000
0100000000
0010000000
0001000000
0000100000
0000010000
0000001000
0000000100
0000000010
0000000001

2. Create a program that will create an X, instead of a diagonal

3. Create a program that will receive input from a user about the size of the array, it will validate it
using try-catch and validating the type and limits, then will create the sample 1, but using the provided
size by the user 
